      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1990: `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()` transforms every loaded text message in one synchronous batch from the load callback path. On large conversations this can block delivery of loaded-message handling and may hand an unbounded vector to plugin code, causing UI stalls or high memory use. Bound the batch size or dispatch work asynchronously in chunks so plugin latency cannot scale linearly with the full loaded history. For example:\n```suggestion\n    constexpr std::size_t maxTransformBatch \u003d 100;\n    for (auto first \u003d batch.begin(); first !\u003d batch.end();) {\n        auto last \u003d std::next(first, std::min(maxTransformBatch, static_cast\u003cstd::size_t\u003e(std::distance(first, batch.end()))));\n        std::vector\u003clibjami::SwarmMessage\u003e chunk(first, last);\n        pluginChatManager.transformSwarmMessages(chunk, accountId_, convId);\n        // write back chunk results\n        first \u003d last;\n    }\n```",
