      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1998: Messages for which the plugin returns no `bodyOverwrite` are never marked as processed. Because the selection condition is `!msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")`, every subsequent load/reload will send the same messages back through the plugin indefinitely, which can be expensive and may repeatedly trigger external translation/service calls. Store an empty sentinel when the transform does not provide an overwrite, just like the empty-overwrite branch already does. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n            const auto boIt \u003d transformed.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n            if (boIt \u003d\u003d transformed.pluginData.end() || boIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n                if (const auto it \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(transformed.id);\n                    it !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n                    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\";\n                }\n                continue;\n            }\n```",
